WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.204 align:middle line:90%
[ Silence ]

00:00:04.204 --> 00:00:13.280 align:middle line:90%
[ Music ]

00:00:28.095 --> 00:00:30.997 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina Meredith: This
story takes us on a wild ride.

00:00:30.997 --> 00:00:34.334 align:middle line:84%
It's about a man who experienced
a rare kundalini awakening

00:00:34.334 --> 00:00:37.804 align:middle line:84%
and decided he wanted to spend
the rest of his life meditating,

00:00:37.804 --> 00:00:39.739 align:middle line:84%
to do that, he needed
enough money

00:00:39.739 --> 00:00:41.575 align:middle line:90%
to take the rest of his life of.

00:00:41.575 --> 00:00:44.711 align:middle line:84%
Understanding focus, awareness
he made millions of dollars

00:00:44.711 --> 00:00:48.048 align:middle line:84%
out of nothing which bought his
freedom to live as he wished.

00:00:48.048 --> 00:00:51.218 align:middle line:84%
From seminary school to
Asian bordellos to true love,

00:00:51.218 --> 00:00:54.488 align:middle line:84%
Marty Birrittella created
a life many only dream off

00:00:54.488 --> 00:00:58.558 align:middle line:84%
to what he says is just
listening and it is.

00:00:58.558 --> 00:01:00.193 align:middle line:90%
I love this book.

00:01:00.193 --> 00:01:01.862 align:middle line:84%
You know how we love just
kind of peeping it on,

00:01:01.862 --> 00:01:03.462 align:middle line:84%
on other people's
live sometimes.

00:01:03.462 --> 00:01:06.600 align:middle line:84%
That's what it's like because
this is-- this is bare.

00:01:06.600 --> 00:01:07.868 align:middle line:90%
>> Martin Birrittella: Yeah.

00:01:07.868 --> 00:01:10.036 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina: You don't-- you
have no gale in the book.

00:01:10.036 --> 00:01:11.471 align:middle line:90%
There's nothing held back.

00:01:11.471 --> 00:01:13.874 align:middle line:84%
It's not like you're
trying to position yourself

00:01:13.874 --> 00:01:15.842 align:middle line:90%
as an angel or a saint.

00:01:15.842 --> 00:01:19.212 align:middle line:84%
And yet at the same time you
have had a chance to rise

00:01:19.212 --> 00:01:22.716 align:middle line:84%
up into this incredibly
angelic experience as a result

00:01:22.716 --> 00:01:24.618 align:middle line:90%
of the path of listening.

00:01:24.618 --> 00:01:26.153 align:middle line:84%
But first of all, before
we get going yesterday--

00:01:26.153 --> 00:01:27.487 align:middle line:90%
>> Martin: OK.

00:01:27.487 --> 00:01:29.656 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina: -- we were-- we
shared a cabin from the airport

00:01:29.656 --> 00:01:31.424 align:middle line:90%
as we came in at the same time.

00:01:31.424 --> 00:01:35.362 align:middle line:84%
And it turns out, you
and the driver, Rob--

00:01:35.362 --> 00:01:37.696 align:middle line:84%
>> Martin: His brother, I played
football with in high school.

00:01:37.696 --> 00:01:38.765 align:middle line:90%
>> Regina: Yes.

00:01:38.765 --> 00:01:40.100 align:middle line:84%
>> Martin: We took
the same high school.

00:01:40.100 --> 00:01:41.368 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina: And it was like
listening to this little slice

00:01:41.368 --> 00:01:43.069 align:middle line:84%
of what I read in your
book about this life

00:01:43.069 --> 00:01:44.204 align:middle line:90%
and Tarrytown New York.

00:01:44.204 --> 00:01:45.272 align:middle line:90%
>> Martin: Right.

00:01:45.272 --> 00:01:46.172 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina: Your families
were intertwined,

00:01:46.172 --> 00:01:47.641 align:middle line:90%
your family's bread business,

00:01:47.641 --> 00:01:49.743 align:middle line:84%
he knew the bread
'cause his family was

00:01:49.743 --> 00:01:50.976 align:middle line:90%
in the restaurant business and--

00:01:50.976 --> 00:01:52.312 align:middle line:90%
>> Martin: Yeah.

00:01:52.312 --> 00:01:54.748 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina: It was like a slice
of life from a certain era

00:01:54.748 --> 00:01:57.050 align:middle line:84%
in New York that only
you two could relate to.

00:01:57.050 --> 00:01:58.885 align:middle line:90%
I was just the observer.

00:01:58.885 --> 00:02:00.187 align:middle line:84%
It was really sweet
to listen to.

00:02:00.187 --> 00:02:01.354 align:middle line:84%
>> Martin: I was--
it was amazing.

00:02:01.354 --> 00:02:02.722 align:middle line:90%
It was amazing.

00:02:02.722 --> 00:02:05.192 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina: So, let's talk about
your life in Tarrytown just

00:02:05.192 --> 00:02:07.260 align:middle line:84%
to set the stage
for what happen,

00:02:07.260 --> 00:02:10.564 align:middle line:84%
because you're an
unlikely person to be--

00:02:10.564 --> 00:02:12.399 align:middle line:90%
well your background is unlikely

00:02:12.399 --> 00:02:14.668 align:middle line:84%
to be one who'd be spending
six hour a day meditating.

00:02:14.668 --> 00:02:16.503 align:middle line:84%
Today, but who's is, right,
if you're in the west.

00:02:16.503 --> 00:02:17.037 align:middle line:90%
>> Martin: Right.

00:02:17.037 --> 00:02:17.571 align:middle line:90%
That's true.

00:02:17.571 --> 00:02:18.705 align:middle line:90%
That's true.

00:02:18.705 --> 00:02:20.173 align:middle line:84%
Well, the funny thing is
in this town, I grow up

00:02:20.173 --> 00:02:22.709 align:middle line:84%
and in my family
there were seven boys.

00:02:22.709 --> 00:02:25.011 align:middle line:84%
Everybody's name began with
an Ms. My mother had seven

00:02:25.011 --> 00:02:31.017 align:middle line:84%
cesareans and she was
very, I wouldn't say wild

00:02:31.017 --> 00:02:32.786 align:middle line:90%
but she was very strict.

00:02:32.786 --> 00:02:34.921 align:middle line:84%
Obviously everybody in
the town knew who we were,

00:02:34.921 --> 00:02:36.690 align:middle line:84%
picture was in the
paper a lot and on top

00:02:36.690 --> 00:02:38.525 align:middle line:90%
of that my dad has this baker

00:02:38.525 --> 00:02:41.927 align:middle line:84%
where everybody buys our
Italian bread all the time.

00:02:41.927 --> 00:02:46.466 align:middle line:84%
And it was just an
amazing place.

00:02:46.466 --> 00:02:48.401 align:middle line:84%
It's a beautiful place to
live and grow up there.

00:02:48.401 --> 00:02:51.438 align:middle line:84%
And me being the second the son,
the oldest was is going to go

00:02:51.438 --> 00:02:54.040 align:middle line:84%
into the bakery business but
I was like, "what could I do

00:02:54.040 --> 00:02:57.377 align:middle line:90%
and my dream in a-- probably

00:02:57.377 --> 00:02:59.946 align:middle line:84%
at that time I was seven years
old is I wanted to be a priest.

00:02:59.946 --> 00:03:03.450 align:middle line:84%
My aunt, my mother's sister
was a nun and I would go

00:03:03.450 --> 00:03:04.751 align:middle line:90%
down to a convent and see that.

00:03:04.751 --> 00:03:06.119 align:middle line:84%
My mother love to
church so much.

00:03:06.119 --> 00:03:08.188 align:middle line:84%
We have big rosaries
hanging in the house.

00:03:08.188 --> 00:03:10.724 align:middle line:84%
And I just loved
everything about the church.

00:03:10.724 --> 00:03:12.525 align:middle line:84%
It was like, I remember
announcing

00:03:12.525 --> 00:03:14.394 align:middle line:84%
to my second grade teacher,
I am going to be a priest

00:03:14.394 --> 00:03:16.162 align:middle line:84%
and by the time I
was 14 years old,

00:03:16.162 --> 00:03:18.498 align:middle line:84%
I went to the junior
seminary to be a priest.

00:03:18.498 --> 00:03:21.134 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina: So, that part of you
was already kicked in by birth.

00:03:21.134 --> 00:03:23.670 align:middle line:84%
I mean you came in
already wired toward--

00:03:23.670 --> 00:03:24.903 align:middle line:90%
>> Martin: Right.

00:03:24.903 --> 00:03:26.439 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina: -- wanting to
experience something of a--

00:03:26.439 --> 00:03:28.975 align:middle line:84%
a more ethereal or
exalted nature.

00:03:28.975 --> 00:03:30.343 align:middle line:84%
>> Martin: Right,
absolutely, absolutely.

00:03:30.343 --> 00:03:31.611 align:middle line:90%
>> Regina: Yeah.

00:03:31.611 --> 00:03:32.946 align:middle line:84%
>> Martin: I mean I always
like to say, I fantasized

00:03:32.946 --> 00:03:34.514 align:middle line:84%
when I was a little kid maybe
9 or 10 years old sitting

00:03:34.514 --> 00:03:37.117 align:middle line:84%
in the church and probably
watching Robin Hood or something

00:03:37.117 --> 00:03:39.986 align:middle line:84%
on TV, I would imagine
myself swing from the balcony

00:03:39.986 --> 00:03:42.322 align:middle line:84%
and saving the priest
because the robbers came

00:03:42.322 --> 00:03:43.623 align:middle line:90%
on to the stage or something.

00:03:43.623 --> 00:03:46.326 align:middle line:84%
So, I had this fantasy going
out on my mind, you know,

00:03:46.326 --> 00:03:48.962 align:middle line:84%
there was sort of--
romantic quality to it

00:03:48.962 --> 00:03:52.132 align:middle line:84%
at the same time but, you know,
sure enough when I was 14,

00:03:52.132 --> 00:03:55.068 align:middle line:84%
you know, I ended up going
away to a Carmelite seminary

00:03:55.068 --> 00:03:58.638 align:middle line:84%
with just 50 kids in it away,
full time, you know, very,

00:03:58.638 --> 00:04:00.173 align:middle line:90%
very strict situation.

00:04:00.173 --> 00:04:01.875 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina: Oh you must have
made your mother very proud.

00:04:01.875 --> 00:04:03.243 align:middle line:90%
>> Martin: Oh she was so happy.

00:04:03.243 --> 00:04:06.579 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina: When I was
seven or eight years old.

00:04:06.579 --> 00:04:08.982 align:middle line:84%
I had dreams of becoming a
nun but I was a Lutheran--

00:04:08.982 --> 00:04:10.350 align:middle line:90%
>> Martin: Yeah.

00:04:10.350 --> 00:04:11.418 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina: -- so I didn't really
understand what was involved

00:04:11.418 --> 00:04:13.052 align:middle line:84%
and after practicing
with my girlfriend,

00:04:13.052 --> 00:04:14.788 align:middle line:84%
all the things Catholics
are supposed to do,

00:04:14.788 --> 00:04:17.991 align:middle line:84%
I realized it was a lot of
work and I bailed a lot sooner

00:04:17.991 --> 00:04:20.160 align:middle line:84%
on that dream of
life that you did.

00:04:20.160 --> 00:04:20.994 align:middle line:90%
>> Martin: Yeah.

00:04:20.994 --> 00:04:21.795 align:middle line:90%
>> Regina: So, seminary school.

00:04:21.795 --> 00:04:22.829 align:middle line:90%
What happened?

00:04:22.829 --> 00:04:24.965 align:middle line:84%
>> Martin: Well, it
was-- I loved it.

00:04:24.965 --> 00:04:27.200 align:middle line:84%
And I was very difficult
'cause I was going

00:04:27.200 --> 00:04:28.969 align:middle line:84%
through puberty at
the same time.

00:04:28.969 --> 00:04:30.637 align:middle line:84%
And there's a lot of
wild things, you know,

00:04:30.637 --> 00:04:32.272 align:middle line:84%
without getting into it,
there's a lot of wild things

00:04:32.272 --> 00:04:35.475 align:middle line:84%
that are going on there
because we would go

00:04:35.475 --> 00:04:39.713 align:middle line:84%
to mass every single morning
and you can't have any sins.

00:04:39.713 --> 00:04:41.314 align:middle line:90%
You have to go to confession.

00:04:41.314 --> 00:04:42.781 align:middle line:84%
I mean literally
to be with a priest

00:04:42.781 --> 00:04:44.351 align:middle line:90%
in the confession every morning.

00:04:44.351 --> 00:04:45.852 align:middle line:84%
When he wasn't there,
I have to go

00:04:45.852 --> 00:04:48.154 align:middle line:84%
down of my dorm,
knock on his door.

00:04:48.154 --> 00:04:49.222 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:04:49.222 --> 00:04:49.889 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina: Were you
there every morning?

00:04:49.889 --> 00:04:50.724 align:middle line:90%
>> Martin: Well, no.

00:04:50.724 --> 00:04:53.326 align:middle line:90%
I wasn't there every morning,

00:04:53.326 --> 00:04:54.928 align:middle line:84%
but I tell you it's a
little traumatic just going

00:04:54.928 --> 00:04:56.963 align:middle line:84%
down there a couple of times
and not knocking on the door

00:04:56.963 --> 00:04:59.099 align:middle line:84%
and say, "Father, can you
hear my confession and kneel

00:04:59.099 --> 00:05:02.102 align:middle line:84%
down next to a bed of
a priest, you know.

00:05:02.102 --> 00:05:03.737 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina: Especially
with today's connotation.

00:05:03.737 --> 00:05:06.573 align:middle line:84%
>> Martin: Yeah, with
today's connotation with that,

00:05:06.573 --> 00:05:07.941 align:middle line:90%
specifically that's not--

00:05:07.941 --> 00:05:10.744 align:middle line:84%
wasn't happening but I did have
a guy end up falling in love

00:05:10.744 --> 00:05:13.246 align:middle line:84%
with me and the reason I
didn't go back to the seminary

00:05:13.246 --> 00:05:16.716 align:middle line:84%
in my second year because
he had sent me a love letter

00:05:16.716 --> 00:05:18.385 align:middle line:90%
and my mother intercepted it

00:05:18.385 --> 00:05:20.754 align:middle line:84%
and when my mother saw
that, she goes, that's it.

00:05:20.754 --> 00:05:23.289 align:middle line:84%
No, you cannot go back to
the seminary so I wouldn't--

00:05:23.289 --> 00:05:25.692 align:middle line:84%
right from my freshmen
year in high school right

00:05:25.692 --> 00:05:29.429 align:middle line:84%
into my Sleepy Hollow High
School which was in Tarrytown

00:05:29.429 --> 00:05:32.265 align:middle line:84%
and I knew all the
kids there already.

00:05:32.265 --> 00:05:33.666 align:middle line:90%
>> Regina: Football, do you.

00:05:33.666 --> 00:05:36.202 align:middle line:84%
>> Martin: Football, I was the
president of the junior class.

00:05:36.202 --> 00:05:38.638 align:middle line:84%
And you know, it was like,
I sort of had a normal life

00:05:38.638 --> 00:05:41.808 align:middle line:84%
from that point forward but I
internally, there was a part

00:05:41.808 --> 00:05:43.943 align:middle line:84%
of me 'cause I was crying
and crying, you know,

00:05:43.943 --> 00:05:45.345 align:middle line:84%
when I couldn't go
back to the seminary,

00:05:45.345 --> 00:05:47.280 align:middle line:90%
I really wanted to do that.

00:05:47.280 --> 00:05:48.281 align:middle line:90%
>> Regina: So divisional--

00:05:48.281 --> 00:05:49.949 align:middle line:84%
to be devoted to
something was really--

00:05:49.949 --> 00:05:50.884 align:middle line:90%
>> Martin: Oh yeah, it was--

00:05:50.884 --> 00:05:52.118 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina: -- high
wired into you.

00:05:52.118 --> 00:05:53.520 align:middle line:84%
>> Martin: It was high
wired into me and, you know,

00:05:53.520 --> 00:05:55.221 align:middle line:90%
I did really well in schools.

00:05:55.221 --> 00:05:57.557 align:middle line:84%
I end up going to Cornell
Engineering School.

00:05:57.557 --> 00:05:59.826 align:middle line:84%
When I was at Cornell,
I only really--

00:05:59.826 --> 00:06:03.129 align:middle line:84%
I lasted there for one year
because one of the things that I

00:06:03.129 --> 00:06:07.000 align:middle line:84%
like to say is that-- besides
everything being a field

00:06:07.000 --> 00:06:09.602 align:middle line:84%
of love, my experience,
everything is a field of love

00:06:09.602 --> 00:06:11.304 align:middle line:84%
that everything is
just movement.

00:06:11.304 --> 00:06:15.608 align:middle line:84%
And one day I was standing
at this war protest in front

00:06:15.608 --> 00:06:18.878 align:middle line:84%
of this famous building,
Willard Straight Hall at Cornell

00:06:18.878 --> 00:06:22.015 align:middle line:84%
and there was a march
over to the--

00:06:22.015 --> 00:06:24.384 align:middle line:84%
they were protesting [inaudible]
and some of the things

00:06:24.384 --> 00:06:25.819 align:middle line:84%
that are going on
at the university.

00:06:25.819 --> 00:06:28.555 align:middle line:84%
I ran into this building where
these people and they took

00:06:28.555 --> 00:06:30.557 align:middle line:90%
over this building and--

00:06:30.557 --> 00:06:32.058 align:middle line:90%
>> Regina: You spontaneously--

00:06:32.058 --> 00:06:33.259 align:middle line:84%
>> Martin: I just
spontaneously--

00:06:33.259 --> 00:06:35.128 align:middle line:84%
it's like something inside
of me just said, move,

00:06:35.128 --> 00:06:37.330 align:middle line:84%
go in this building and
instantly they're chaining

00:06:37.330 --> 00:06:40.300 align:middle line:84%
up the doors and
wallpapering everything.

00:06:40.300 --> 00:06:43.570 align:middle line:84%
There was just crazy
takeover and, you know,

00:06:43.570 --> 00:06:47.040 align:middle line:84%
within a few hours or 30,
riot polices coming down

00:06:47.040 --> 00:06:49.309 align:middle line:84%
and breaking the windows,
they're coming in,

00:06:49.309 --> 00:06:51.611 align:middle line:84%
but what happened was
since the president

00:06:51.611 --> 00:06:54.314 align:middle line:84%
of the university wasn't there,
we ended up holding on to

00:06:54.314 --> 00:06:57.417 align:middle line:84%
that building for--
for a whole week.

00:06:57.417 --> 00:06:58.351 align:middle line:90%
>> Regina: That made the news.

00:06:58.351 --> 00:06:59.552 align:middle line:90%
>> Martin: That made the news.

00:06:59.552 --> 00:07:01.354 align:middle line:84%
I was on news, and they
came to us and they said--

00:07:01.354 --> 00:07:04.624 align:middle line:84%
Attica, amount people or
listeners know what Attica was

00:07:04.624 --> 00:07:07.427 align:middle line:84%
but that was like maybe 9
months before that they sent

00:07:07.427 --> 00:07:08.795 align:middle line:90%
in 500 state troopers.

00:07:08.795 --> 00:07:12.298 align:middle line:84%
A lot of inmates got killed
there so they just said to us.

00:07:12.298 --> 00:07:14.667 align:middle line:84%
It's like, you either out
of this building by Friday,

00:07:14.667 --> 00:07:16.169 align:middle line:84%
if you're not we're sending
all these state troopers

00:07:16.169 --> 00:07:17.437 align:middle line:90%
down here, so were smart enough.

00:07:17.437 --> 00:07:19.239 align:middle line:84%
Even though they--
they held tripods set

00:07:19.239 --> 00:07:22.408 align:middle line:84%
up across the street taking
photographs of everybody.

00:07:22.408 --> 00:07:24.611 align:middle line:84%
And instead of getting
kicked out of school

00:07:24.611 --> 00:07:29.582 align:middle line:84%
which many people did, I just
left and dropped out of Cornell

00:07:29.582 --> 00:07:30.683 align:middle line:90%
and I went to work

00:07:30.683 --> 00:07:32.285 align:middle line:84%
as a construction worker
in Albany, New York.

00:07:32.285 --> 00:07:34.187 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina: But that's where
it really gets interesting.

00:07:34.187 --> 00:07:35.021 align:middle line:90%
>> Martin: Yeah.

00:07:35.021 --> 00:07:36.322 align:middle line:90%
>> Regina: Let me just go back.

00:07:36.322 --> 00:07:39.858 align:middle line:84%
For a moment, my mind has
always wondered about this.

00:07:39.858 --> 00:07:43.229 align:middle line:84%
You put a bunch of young
pubescent boys together,

00:07:43.229 --> 00:07:45.899 align:middle line:84%
sequestered, cloistered,
no girls,

00:07:45.899 --> 00:07:49.102 align:middle line:84%
you can't have any interaction
with girls, how's a system

00:07:49.102 --> 00:07:51.204 align:middle line:90%
like that ever going to work?

00:07:51.204 --> 00:07:53.206 align:middle line:90%
I mean that just doesn't work.

00:07:53.206 --> 00:07:54.406 align:middle line:84%
>> Martin: Well, I don't
know if that's true.

00:07:54.406 --> 00:07:56.242 align:middle line:84%
I mean you can see like
in this Buddha's monastery

00:07:56.242 --> 00:07:59.178 align:middle line:84%
in the far east going to
Thailand and Indonesia

00:07:59.178 --> 00:08:01.614 align:middle line:84%
and places like there's like,
you know, hundred and hundreds

00:08:01.614 --> 00:08:02.815 align:middle line:90%
so that can totally work.

00:08:02.815 --> 00:08:04.717 align:middle line:84%
I just think it's--
it totally can work.

00:08:04.717 --> 00:08:06.052 align:middle line:84%
It's totally the
mindset of that.

00:08:06.052 --> 00:08:08.354 align:middle line:84%
It's just that, you know,
I'm hearing like everybody is

00:08:08.354 --> 00:08:10.089 align:middle line:84%
