He's like, "Where is"--

00:30:07.272 --> 00:30:09.241 align:middle line:84%
you know, "Where is this
girl Tara [assumed spelling]?

00:30:09.241 --> 00:30:10.508 align:middle line:90%
You know, "Where is she?"

00:30:10.508 --> 00:30:13.645 align:middle line:84%
And I'm going, "I
don't, you know?

00:30:13.645 --> 00:30:14.713 align:middle line:90%
He doesn't even say that.

00:30:14.713 --> 00:30:16.815 align:middle line:84%
He just like almost
foaming at the mouth

00:30:16.815 --> 00:30:18.650 align:middle line:84%
and this other girl
runs in and he goes,

00:30:18.650 --> 00:30:19.885 align:middle line:90%
you know, "Where is Tara?"

00:30:19.885 --> 00:30:21.419 align:middle line:84%
And I go, "I don't know"
and she looks up, bothered,

00:30:21.419 --> 00:30:22.854 align:middle line:84%
and looks back at
me and she goes,

00:30:22.854 --> 00:30:24.656 align:middle line:84%
"That's the wrong
answer," you know.

00:30:24.656 --> 00:30:25.657 align:middle line:90%
>> Regina: Yeah.

00:30:25.657 --> 00:30:26.358 align:middle line:84%
>> Martin: Like he
knew I knew that.

00:30:26.358 --> 00:30:26.925 align:middle line:90%
He knew where she was.

00:30:26.925 --> 00:30:28.026 align:middle line:90%
>> Regina: Yeah.

00:30:28.026 --> 00:30:29.027 align:middle line:84%
>> Martin: He was--
you know, so by that--

00:30:29.027 --> 00:30:30.428 align:middle line:84%
it's like those types
of interactions.

00:30:30.428 --> 00:30:32.063 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina: Well, you ended up
as kind of a security guard--

00:30:32.063 --> 00:30:33.365 align:middle line:90%
>> Martin: Well, yeah.

00:30:33.365 --> 00:30:34.199 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina: -- so to speak
for the facility after that.

00:30:34.199 --> 00:30:34.833 align:middle line:90%
>> Martin: Well, a little bit.

00:30:34.833 --> 00:30:35.533 align:middle line:90%
>> Regina: Yeah.

00:30:35.533 --> 00:30:36.101 align:middle line:90%
>> Martin: I look back--

00:30:36.101 --> 00:30:36.935 align:middle line:90%
>> Regina: Yeah.

00:30:36.935 --> 00:30:37.502 align:middle line:90%
You kind of you kept the order.

00:30:37.502 --> 00:30:38.703 align:middle line:90%
>> Martin: Yeah.

00:30:38.703 --> 00:30:40.305 align:middle line:84%
Yeah. And then, really
the most significant thing

00:30:40.305 --> 00:30:41.773 align:middle line:84%
that happened was
after I was there

00:30:41.773 --> 00:30:45.610 align:middle line:84%
for six months some girl walks
into the little juice bar

00:30:45.610 --> 00:30:49.080 align:middle line:84%
and says, "You want to
have some ice cream?"

00:30:49.080 --> 00:30:54.319 align:middle line:84%
And her name was Sherry [assumed
spelling] and three days later,

00:30:54.319 --> 00:30:56.888 align:middle line:84%
I'm sitting in the
evening program, all right,

00:30:56.888 --> 00:30:58.757 align:middle line:84%
sitting there, meditating
and I can hear this voice,

00:30:58.757 --> 00:30:59.991 align:middle line:90%
"Ask that girl to marry you."

00:30:59.991 --> 00:31:01.960 align:middle line:90%
I was like, "No way."

00:31:01.960 --> 00:31:03.428 align:middle line:90%
"No. Are you out of your minds?"

00:31:03.428 --> 00:31:05.130 align:middle line:84%
It's like, "Ask this
girl to marry you?"

00:31:05.130 --> 00:31:07.766 align:middle line:84%
So I actually got up
in darshan [phonetic],

00:31:07.766 --> 00:31:09.701 align:middle line:84%
everybody standing there
with their fruits or bananas

00:31:09.701 --> 00:31:10.735 align:middle line:90%
and flowers and everything,

00:31:10.735 --> 00:31:12.504 align:middle line:84%
a big one wine going
up to Muktananda.

00:31:12.504 --> 00:31:14.372 align:middle line:84%
I walked up to this
girl and I say,

00:31:14.372 --> 00:31:15.240 align:middle line:90%
you know, "Will you marry me?"

00:31:15.240 --> 00:31:17.108 align:middle line:90%
And she says, "Yes," all right.

00:31:17.108 --> 00:31:20.245 align:middle line:84%
Get to the final line and Baba's
like, he's hitting us like yes,

00:31:20.245 --> 00:31:21.680 align:middle line:84%
get married a very
nice wedding which is

00:31:21.680 --> 00:31:23.415 align:middle line:90%
like in two weeks, you know?

00:31:23.415 --> 00:31:24.849 align:middle line:84%
People don't even know
who this girl was.

00:31:24.849 --> 00:31:27.185 align:middle line:84%
It's like I hardly even
knew who this girl was.

00:31:27.185 --> 00:31:30.288 align:middle line:84%
And he used to like-- Baba used
to love to tell stories like,

00:31:30.288 --> 00:31:32.724 align:middle line:84%
"You can meet somebody in
the back of the darshan line

