00:38:05.583 --> 00:38:06.818 align:middle line:90%
into starting Rebook.

00:38:06.818 --> 00:38:10.521 align:middle line:84%
And then L.A. Gear, Bob
Greenberg was a hairdresser

00:38:10.521 --> 00:38:12.123 align:middle line:84%
in the same town I was
living in at the time,

00:38:12.123 --> 00:38:14.392 align:middle line:90%
Newton but he was out in Venice.

00:38:14.392 --> 00:38:15.693 align:middle line:84%
Both of those guys
took companies

00:38:15.693 --> 00:38:17.862 align:middle line:90%
to a billion dollars in sales.

00:38:17.862 --> 00:38:18.963 align:middle line:90%
And they didn't know--

00:38:18.963 --> 00:38:19.731 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina: And they
didn't know anything.

00:38:19.731 --> 00:38:20.865 align:middle line:90%
So you were qualified too.

00:38:20.865 --> 00:38:21.532 align:middle line:84%
>> Martin: -- that's why
I said I was qualified.

00:38:21.532 --> 00:38:22.633 align:middle line:90%
I'm from Newton.

00:38:22.633 --> 00:38:23.901 align:middle line:84%
I know nothing about
the footwear business.

00:38:23.901 --> 00:38:25.536 align:middle line:90%
This must be perfect, you know?

00:38:25.536 --> 00:38:26.904 align:middle line:90%
>> Regina: Right.

00:38:26.904 --> 00:38:28.473 align:middle line:84%
>> Martin: So I basically--
and I saw I needed to come up.

00:38:28.473 --> 00:38:30.575 align:middle line:84%
So the name of the company
that we came up with was Ryka.

00:38:30.575 --> 00:38:32.477 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina: And you and your
wife started it together?

00:38:32.477 --> 00:38:33.878 align:middle line:90%
>> Martin: We-- that's right.

00:38:33.878 --> 00:38:36.748 align:middle line:84%
And RYKA, R-Y-K-A, my mother's
maiden name was Riker, R-I-K-E-R

00:38:36.748 --> 00:38:39.083 align:middle line:84%
but we go, "We need to
make it a little bit--

00:38:39.083 --> 00:38:40.284 align:middle line:90%
you know, European-look."

00:38:40.284 --> 00:38:43.354 align:middle line:84%
So we did R-Y-K-A and put
two umlauts over the A

00:38:43.354 --> 00:38:45.790 align:middle line:84%
to make it look like Haagen-Dazs
and those were the logos

00:38:45.790 --> 00:38:47.325 align:middle line:90%
on the back of the shoes.

00:38:47.325 --> 00:38:53.264 align:middle line:84%
And probably I'd say
only a year and a half

00:38:53.264 --> 00:38:55.066 align:middle line:84%
after starting the
idea of this company,

00:38:55.066 --> 00:38:57.402 align:middle line:90%
the company had no sales at all.

00:38:57.402 --> 00:39:04.275 align:middle line:84%
And we took the company
public on February 12th, 1988.

00:39:04.275 --> 00:39:05.643 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina: OK, so I
want to talk about that.

00:39:05.643 --> 00:39:06.778 align:middle line:84%
>> Martin: OK, OK,
let's talk about--

00:39:06.778 --> 00:39:08.112 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina: Because one
of the funniest stories

00:39:08.112 --> 00:39:12.884 align:middle line:84%
in the book is people don't
understand how manifestation

00:39:12.884 --> 00:39:14.252 align:middle line:90%
works in general.

00:39:14.252 --> 00:39:17.221 align:middle line:84%
Where all as a species
beginning to learn

00:39:17.221 --> 00:39:18.556 align:middle line:90%
that this is our creation--

00:39:18.556 --> 00:39:19.757 align:middle line:90%
>> Martin: Yeah.

00:39:19.757 --> 00:39:21.159 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina: -- and we can
create it the way we want.

00:39:21.159 --> 00:39:22.960 align:middle line:84%
And it doesn't have to look like
anything out of out a textbook

00:39:22.960 --> 00:39:24.829 align:middle line:90%
or like anybody else's canvas.

00:39:24.829 --> 00:39:28.199 align:middle line:84%
And you already knew that
because you're understanding

00:39:28.199 --> 00:39:31.135 align:middle line:84%
in your meditation and those
sublime experiences you had had

00:39:31.135 --> 00:39:32.870 align:middle line:90%
is that it's already here.

00:39:32.870 --> 00:39:34.005 align:middle line:90%
>> Martin: That's right.

00:39:34.005 --> 00:39:34.772 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina: In a sense
it's already happened.

00:39:34.772 --> 00:39:35.573 align:middle line:90%
You have to walk into it.

00:39:35.573 --> 00:39:36.340 align:middle line:90%
>> Martin: That's right.

00:39:36.340 --> 00:39:37.675 align:middle line:90%
>> Regina: And that is key

00:39:37.675 --> 00:39:39.010 align:middle line:84%
because most people
don't feel it.

00:39:39.010 --> 00:39:40.244 align:middle line:90%
It's already happened.

00:39:40.244 --> 00:39:43.448 align:middle line:84%
So tell us a story about
having to go to your meeting

00:39:43.448 --> 00:39:47.585 align:middle line:84%
to get this kind of incredible
monetary support and backing

00:39:47.585 --> 00:39:50.054 align:middle line:84%
with nothing but a drawing
from your babysitter.

00:39:50.054 --> 00:39:50.788 align:middle line:90%
>> Martin: That's right.

00:39:50.788 --> 00:39:52.089 align:middle line:90%
>> Regina: I love this.

00:39:52.089 --> 00:39:54.725 align:middle line:84%
>> Martin: So I-- you know,
I was just like sitting

00:39:54.725 --> 00:39:56.394 align:middle line:84%
in a house one day I
thought like, well--

00:39:56.394 --> 00:39:59.797 align:middle line:84%
you know, I need
besides the Ryka name,

00:39:59.797 --> 00:40:00.965 align:middle line:84%
we need like another
cachet or something--

00:40:00.965 --> 00:40:02.166 align:middle line:90%
>> Regina: How about a picture.

00:40:02.166 --> 00:40:03.701 align:middle line:84%
>> Martin: OK, picture
of or something like this

00:40:03.701 --> 00:40:06.070 align:middle line:84%
when I get the idea, I was
like, call the U.S. Ski team up,

00:40:06.070 --> 00:40:07.405 align:middle line:90%
you know, so they have dry--

00:40:07.405 --> 00:40:10.208 align:middle line:84%
at the time cross training
was a big thing so I was like,

00:40:10.208 --> 00:40:13.778 align:middle line:84%
let's do cross training shoes
and I called the U.S. Ski team,

00:40:13.778 --> 00:40:15.346 align:middle line:84%
can we be the official--
I didn't even have a shoe.

00:40:15.346 --> 00:40:16.981 align:middle line:84%
I didn't even have
a drawing of a shoe.

00:40:16.981 --> 00:40:19.784 align:middle line:84%
And the guy from Subaru had
just moved over from Subaru

00:40:19.784 --> 00:40:21.185 align:middle line:84%
to the U.S. Ski team,
he goes come

00:40:21.185 --> 00:40:22.453 align:middle line:84%
down to the Waldorf
[phonetic], if I'm going to be

00:40:22.453 --> 00:40:24.555 align:middle line:84%
in New York next week
I fly down there.

00:40:24.555 --> 00:40:27.258 align:middle line:84%
I didn't have any things
so I have my baby sitter

00:40:27.258 --> 00:40:29.961 align:middle line:84%
who would have-- it was like
somewhat of a kid artist,

00:40:29.961 --> 00:40:31.429 align:middle line:90%
I said, Nancy drew their shoes."

00:40:31.429 --> 00:40:33.931 align:middle line:84%
So I went-- literally went
down, it's like in a lobby

00:40:33.931 --> 00:40:36.767 align:middle line:84%
of the Waldorf with a
shoe, a drawing of shoe.

00:40:36.767 --> 00:40:39.704 align:middle line:84%
I had a letter from
Moore Shoe [phonetic]

00:40:39.704 --> 00:40:42.173 align:middle line:84%
who actually was making
L.A. Gear shoes also saying

00:40:42.173 --> 00:40:43.641 align:middle line:84%
that they would make
their shoes for us.

00:40:43.641 --> 00:40:45.276 align:middle line:84%
And I was sitting there
and I said, "You know,

00:40:45.276 --> 00:40:46.811 align:middle line:84%
I want to be the
official training shoe."

00:40:46.811 --> 00:40:49.747 align:middle line:84%
He goes, "Give me cheque
for 5000 dollars right now

00:40:49.747 --> 00:40:52.383 align:middle line:84%
and I'll give you
a seven year deal."

00:40:52.383 --> 00:40:53.417 align:middle line:90%
You know, boom, just like that.

00:40:53.417 --> 00:40:55.253 align:middle line:90%
I just took all the money I had.

00:40:55.253 --> 00:40:57.655 align:middle line:84%
I know it just like-- just about
the total-- my total savings.

00:40:57.655 --> 00:40:58.923 align:middle line:84%
I wrote a cheque
and gave to him.

00:40:58.923 --> 00:41:01.125 align:middle line:84%
I was like ecstatic
in the cab going back

00:41:01.125 --> 00:41:04.862 align:middle line:84%
to take the shuttle back
to Boston and that sort

00:41:04.862 --> 00:41:09.867 align:middle line:84%
of catapulted us to get an
underwriter who was in Denver,

00:41:09.867 --> 00:41:12.937 align:middle line:84%
all right, who there was a
female partner who owned it

00:41:12.937 --> 00:41:15.806 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina: And they did on this
picture of a shoe in an idea.

00:41:15.806 --> 00:41:17.041 align:middle line:84%
>> Martin: What they
did with shoe and I--

00:41:17.041 --> 00:41:18.709 align:middle line:84%
my ex-wife Sherry [assumed
spelling] was the--

00:41:18.709 --> 00:41:21.712 align:middle line:84%
she's the most fantastic
sales person in the world

00:41:21.712 --> 00:41:25.483 align:middle line:84%
and we said our advertising
agency would suggest to us,

00:41:25.483 --> 00:41:27.485 align:middle line:84%
why don't you just do--
for woman by woman,

00:41:27.485 --> 00:41:29.320 align:middle line:84%
just to make it a
women's only company.

00:41:29.320 --> 00:41:31.289 align:middle line:84%
So the investment
banker was like OK.

00:41:31.289 --> 00:41:34.358 align:middle line:84%
They said to me-- you know,
start selling baby food--

00:41:34.358 --> 00:41:38.796 align:middle line:84%
you know, I would do that only
because I just like listen

00:41:38.796 --> 00:41:40.364 align:middle line:90%
to what's the next thing to do.

00:41:40.364 --> 00:41:41.732 align:middle line:84%
It's like always-- one
of the things I say

00:41:41.732 --> 00:41:42.533 align:middle line:90%
on the book it's that--

00:41:42.533 --> 00:41:43.734 align:middle line:90%
>> Regina: When you meditate

00:41:43.734 --> 00:41:44.802 align:middle line:84%
>> Martin: When I meditate
it's like say is a law,

00:41:44.802 --> 00:41:46.904 align:middle line:84%
instead of a law
attraction, I'm saying it,

00:41:46.904 --> 00:41:47.838 align:middle line:90%
the law of distraction.

00:41:47.838 --> 00:41:50.007 align:middle line:90%
I say just stay with yourself,

00:41:50.007 --> 00:41:53.811 align:middle line:84%
your heart already knows
what it wants and it needs.

00:41:53.811 --> 00:41:55.212 align:middle line:90%
It doesn't need any prompting.

00:41:55.212 --> 00:41:58.349 align:middle line:84%
It doesn't need any visions just
listen and it will just send you

00:41:58.349 --> 00:42:00.851 align:middle line:84%
in a direction because it
really wants to give it to you.

00:42:00.851 --> 00:42:03.988 align:middle line:84%
You know that's problem one of
the biggest messages in the book

00:42:03.988 --> 00:42:05.456 align:middle line:90%
and allow, which is to happen

00:42:05.456 --> 00:42:09.026 align:middle line:84%
in its own time frame
and don't judge it.

00:42:09.026 --> 00:42:13.230 align:middle line:84%
So we ended up taking that
company public and instantly,

00:42:13.230 --> 00:42:16.067 align:middle line:84%
you know as the company goes
publicly we're both have tons

00:42:16.067 --> 00:42:19.003 align:middle line:84%
of money which we didn't
have before, and you know--

00:42:19.003 --> 00:42:20.204 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina: How old
are you at this time?

00:42:20.204 --> 00:42:22.273 align:middle line:90%
>> Martin: I'm like 30.

00:42:22.273 --> 00:42:23.975 align:middle line:90%
I was like 35.

00:42:23.975 --> 00:42:25.743 align:middle line:90%
I was 35 year old.

00:42:25.743 --> 00:42:27.745 align:middle line:84%
We're both basically
the same age.

00:42:27.745 --> 00:42:30.181 align:middle line:84%
And my dream, I was, "Oh,
I just want to meditate."

00:42:30.181 --> 00:42:32.450 align:middle line:84%
So it's like all of a sudden,
it's like, I'm going in my room

00:42:32.450 --> 00:42:35.152 align:middle line:84%
to meditate and my
ex-wife was like,

00:42:35.152 --> 00:42:36.554 align:middle line:90%
she had other things to do.

00:42:36.554 --> 00:42:37.555 align:middle line:90%
>> Regina: Right.

00:42:37.555 --> 00:42:38.222 align:middle line:84%
>> Martin: She didn't
have any money.

00:42:38.222 --> 00:42:39.023 align:middle line:90%
It's like, you know?

00:42:39.023 --> 00:42:40.224 align:middle line:90%
>> Regina: Yeah, you got--

00:42:40.224 --> 00:42:42.326 align:middle line:84%
didn't have any money and
now you have tons of it.

00:42:42.326 --> 00:42:43.894 align:middle line:84%
>> Martin: Yeah, I had
tons of it so I was like--

00:42:43.894 --> 00:42:46.364 align:middle line:84%
but the thing that happened
is sort of like it ended

00:42:46.364 --> 00:42:49.000 align:middle line:84%
up splitting us apart 'cause she
want one way and the other way

00:42:49.000 --> 00:42:51.068 align:middle line:84%
and it's like, we ended
up getting divorce.

00:42:51.068 --> 00:42:54.005 align:middle line:84%
And it was like, she's not
going to leave the company

00:42:54.005 --> 00:42:56.073 align:middle line:84%
because now we're basically
based the whole image

00:42:56.073 --> 00:42:59.343 align:middle line:84%
of the company around her as the
president so I was like, "Oh,

00:42:59.343 --> 00:43:00.411 align:middle line:84%
just go take another
[inaudible]."

00:43:00.411 --> 00:43:01.912 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina: Right, yeah
a woman on company

00:43:01.912 --> 00:43:03.180 align:middle line:90%
and a product for women.

00:43:03.180 --> 00:43:04.482 align:middle line:90%
>> Martin: That's right.

00:43:04.482 --> 00:43:05.750 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina: And I remember
buying Ryka shoes back then

00:43:05.750 --> 00:43:06.717 align:middle line:90%
because I used to run a lot.

00:43:06.717 --> 00:43:08.085 align:middle line:90%
>> Martin: Yeah, and she--

00:43:08.085 --> 00:43:10.588 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina: And I thought, what's
different from a woman shoe

00:43:10.588 --> 00:43:13.124 align:middle line:84%
from a man shoe but it
sounds cool, I'm buying it.

00:43:13.124 --> 00:43:14.191 align:middle line:90%
>> Martin: Exactly.

00:43:14.191 --> 00:43:15.559 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina: So, whatever
it is, it worked.

00:43:15.559 --> 00:43:16.827 align:middle line:84%
>> Martin: Exactly, it worked
great and she was on Oprah,

00:43:16.827 --> 00:43:19.764 align:middle line:84%
she was on Today's Show,
they were in People Magazine.

00:43:19.764 --> 00:43:22.967 align:middle line:84%
I was so happy, it was like
ecstatic and it's like, OK,

00:43:22.967 --> 00:43:25.069 align:middle line:90%
let me go do another company.

00:43:25.069 --> 00:43:26.203 align:middle line:90%
So I couldn't do anything woman,

00:43:26.203 --> 00:43:28.272 align:middle line:84%
so I did this men's
intercity shoe--

00:43:28.272 --> 00:43:29.273 align:middle line:90%
>> Regina: I loved the poster.

00:43:29.273 --> 00:43:30.441 align:middle line:90%
>> Martin: Yeah, aerial assault.

00:43:30.441 --> 00:43:31.876 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina: Yeah,
that you pay in it.

00:43:31.876 --> 00:43:33.077 align:middle line:90%
>> Martin: Yeah, aerial assault.

00:43:33.077 --> 00:43:35.446 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina: And you
had people clamoring

00:43:35.446 --> 00:43:38.683 align:middle line:84%
for the product before
the product ever existed?

00:43:38.683 --> 00:43:39.950 align:middle line:84%
>> Martin: Yeah, we
were saying that,

00:43:39.950 --> 00:43:42.053 align:middle line:84%
it's like earlier before
we started filming,

00:43:42.053 --> 00:43:45.322 align:middle line:84%
I was telling the story of how,
we had all the samples made

00:43:45.322 --> 00:43:49.060 align:middle line:84%
in leather jackets and hats,
you know, it's aerial assault,

00:43:49.060 --> 00:43:50.394 align:middle line:90%
a big black letter assault.

00:43:50.394 --> 00:43:53.831 align:middle line:84%
It was all really edgies but
we went down into the ghetto

00:43:53.831 --> 00:43:57.001 align:middle line:84%
in New York and lay the-- all
the product out in the street,

00:43:57.001 --> 00:43:58.736 align:middle line:84%
in front of the stores 'cause
[inaudible] in the stores

00:43:58.736 --> 00:44:01.605 align:middle line:84%
when the kids go there, the gets
went literally they went crazy.

00:44:01.605 --> 00:44:03.007 align:middle line:90%
You know, looking at this stuff

00:44:03.007 --> 00:44:06.444 align:middle line:84%
that this investment banker
was standing there, looking,

00:44:06.444 --> 00:44:08.512 align:middle line:84%
you know, he was like, he
couldn't believe this one,

00:44:08.512 --> 00:44:11.348 align:middle line:84%
an older man walked up and say,
"You see that leather jacket.

00:44:11.348 --> 00:44:14.051 align:middle line:84%
If I have the [inaudible]
I'm a dead man."

00:44:14.051 --> 00:44:17.922 align:middle line:84%
I freaked out the investment
banker so much, he goes, "Whoa!"

00:44:17.922 --> 00:44:21.992 align:middle line:84%
I cannot take this company
public and so what am I going

00:44:21.992 --> 00:44:23.194 align:middle line:90%
to do-- I just listened again,

00:44:23.194 --> 00:44:25.196 align:middle line:84%
this is another example,
just listening.

00:44:25.196 --> 00:44:27.965 align:middle line:84%
I was like, I called the
United Negro College fund

00:44:27.965 --> 00:44:30.901 align:middle line:84%
and the National Urban League
and I went to them and said,

00:44:30.901 --> 00:44:34.105 align:middle line:84%
"Will you let us put
your logos on our boxes

00:44:34.105 --> 00:44:37.208 align:middle line:84%
and we'll give you five percent
of the profits of the company

00:44:37.208 --> 00:44:39.076 align:middle line:84%
to those organization
and I go, where they are?

00:44:39.076 --> 00:44:40.277 align:middle line:90%
We'll do it.

00:44:40.277 --> 00:44:42.113 align:middle line:84%
I was like shock that they
would do but I just got

00:44:42.113 --> 00:44:45.916 align:middle line:84%
that just got back just totally
from listening and that we end

00:44:45.916 --> 00:44:47.384 align:middle line:90%
up getting another underwriter

00:44:47.384 --> 00:44:49.453 align:middle line:84%
and then I took that
company public.

00:44:49.453 --> 00:44:52.490 align:middle line:84%
And as soon as that company went
public, it was sort of like,

00:44:52.490 --> 00:44:55.192 align:middle line:90%
I was home free at that point.

00:44:55.192 --> 00:44:56.393 align:middle line:90%
I was like--

00:44:56.393 --> 00:44:57.561 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina: As a young you
do didn't need to worry.

00:44:57.561 --> 00:44:58.863 align:middle line:84%
>> Martin: Yeah, yeah,
yeah, that was-- yeah.

00:44:58.863 --> 00:45:00.664 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina: So why
did you do it again?

00:45:00.664 --> 00:45:02.233 align:middle line:90%
>> Martin: Well, now Id had--

00:45:02.233 --> 00:45:04.034 align:middle line:84%
after Aerial Assault
went public, I was like,

00:45:04.034 --> 00:45:05.102 align:middle line:90%
that was it, that was it for me.

00:45:05.102 --> 00:45:06.036 align:middle line:90%
I basically stopped working.

00:45:06.036 --> 00:45:09.340 align:middle line:90%
That was like, 1993.

00:45:09.340 --> 00:45:11.742 align:middle line:84%
So now what ends up
happening is now--

00:45:11.742 --> 00:45:14.612 align:middle line:84%
after the second company goes
public and I'm totally retired,

00:45:14.612 --> 00:45:18.582 align:middle line:84%
I go, I'm going to build a
big, you know, mansion temple

00:45:18.582 --> 00:45:22.520 align:middle line:84%
and the statue of
Nityananda that Muktananda has

00:45:22.520 --> 00:45:25.356 align:middle line:84%
and his [foreign language],
I'm going to get that statue

00:45:25.356 --> 00:45:29.627 align:middle line:84%
who I had young Nityananda, this
other kid make for me, you know,

00:45:29.627 --> 00:45:31.762 align:middle line:84%
had it made it for me,
the identical statue.

00:45:31.762 --> 00:45:33.431 align:middle line:90%
And I have this temple now.

00:45:33.431 --> 00:45:35.065 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina: Well he was the
guru of Muktananda, right?

00:45:35.065 --> 00:45:36.033 align:middle line:90%
>> Martin: No, no.

00:45:36.033 --> 00:45:37.168 align:middle line:84%
